        <bioghist id="ref4">
            <head>Historical/Biographical Note</head>
            <p>The Co-Operative Educational Instite Association in the Brownsville neighborhood of Brooklyn, New York City, administered a cooperative evening school offering high school equivalency courses. The students selected their teachers, decided on their curriculum and fees, and elected their administrative officers.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent id="ref1">
            <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
            <p>The records consist of reports, minutes, schedules, and correspondence that document the life of the school. Many of the letters are to John L. Afras, registrar and English teacher. Also included is correspondence with the Co-operative League of America.</p>
